bodyV2.markdown:
Les Misérables is one of the longest-running musicals in the West-End for a reason; the score is full of some of the greatest songs in musical history. Some of the most well-known are: “I Dreamed a Dream”, “One Day More”, “On My Own”, “Bring Him Home”, “Do You Hear the People Sing?”, “Who Am I?”, “Empty Chairs at Empty Tables”, “Stars”, and “A Heart Full of Love”.
